1
00:00:35,099 --> 00:00:36,237
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:36,237 --> 00:00:37,155
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:37,155 --> 00:00:38,247
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:39,526 --> 00:00:42,985
[Gyeongseong Love Song]
With this, I'm thinking of making a movie.

5
00:00:44,059 --> 00:00:46,104
But it doesn't have an ending.

6
00:00:46,104 --> 00:00:48,070
Work on it with me.

7
00:00:52,895 --> 00:00:56,828
You shouldn't have come back
acting as if nothing had happened!

8
00:00:58,035 --> 00:01:01,073
You should've just remained my first love.

9
00:01:01,073 --> 00:01:03,198
Not my biggest regret.

10
00:01:03,785 --> 00:01:07,255
<i>My first love, who grew by feeding on my dream,</i>

11
00:01:07,255 --> 00:01:09,674
<i>Woo Soo Bin</i>

12
00:01:09,674 --> 00:01:11,577
<i>has returned.</i>

13
00:02:35,343 --> 00:02:38,251
Cut! Cut!

14
00:02:38,251 --> 00:02:40,051
Lights on!

15
00:02:40,798 --> 00:02:42,878
That was good. Why?

16
00:02:43,844 --> 00:02:46,521
Why would you hold a flashlight?

17
00:02:46,521 --> 00:02:48,040
They do in movies.

18
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:50,108
That's what you call a cliché.

19
00:02:50,108 --> 00:02:52,176
What's a cliché?

20
00:02:52,176 --> 00:02:54,020
What's with the blood makeup?

21
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:55,646
Woo Soo Bin!

22
00:02:55,646 --> 00:02:57,096
Yeah?

23
00:02:57,096 --> 00:03:00,336
Why do you keep spinning that?

24
00:03:00,336 --> 00:03:03,187
You told me to keep spinning it.

25
00:03:04,099 --> 00:03:06,196
Should I reverse it?

26
00:03:06,196 --> 00:03:08,220
Where's the cat?

27
00:03:08,220 --> 00:03:09,503
Kitty.

28
00:03:09,503 --> 00:03:13,011
I think that's enough makeup...

29
00:03:13,011 --> 00:03:16,037
I have a cram school soon.

30
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:19,650
It's perfect now.

31
00:03:20,504 --> 00:03:23,217
- Thanks.
- Sure.

32
00:03:26,688 --> 00:03:28,438
Makeup's done.

33
00:03:28,438 --> 00:03:31,278
Yi Jae, I can't find the cat.

34
00:03:31,278 --> 00:03:34,258
Fine. We already shot the cat scene.

35
00:03:35,403 --> 00:03:39,219
This scene feels flat.

36
00:03:41,058 --> 00:03:43,084
It needs a punch.

37
00:03:52,842 --> 00:03:54,374
Here.

38
00:03:54,374 --> 00:03:56,807
You shoot the next take.

39
00:03:56,807 --> 00:03:58,337
Me?

40
00:03:58,337 --> 00:04:00,189
You get the vibe, huh?

41
00:04:01,767 --> 00:04:03,407
Yeah.

42
00:04:05,475 --> 00:04:08,209
I'm dying here.

43
00:04:08,209 --> 00:04:09,479
My shoulder...

44
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:11,338
Seriously...

45
00:04:11,338 --> 00:04:12,858
He's even worse.

46
00:04:12,858 --> 00:04:15,451
Isn't this makeup a bit much?

47
00:04:15,451 --> 00:04:17,085
Ready!

48
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:22,375
Woo Soo Bin, you ready?

49
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:23,607
Yeah.

50
00:04:23,607 --> 00:04:25,203
Okay.

51
00:04:25,203 --> 00:04:26,960
Action!

52
00:04:40,302 --> 00:04:45,051
<i>What kind of world does she live in?</i>

53
00:04:50,091 --> 00:04:52,345
<i>What she likes,</i>

54
00:04:57,363 --> 00:04:59,477
<i>what she sees,</i>

55
00:05:06,084 --> 00:05:08,452
<i>what she says...</i>

56
00:05:17,339 --> 00:05:20,252
<i>I wanted to know it all.</i>

57
00:05:26,957 --> 00:05:29,060
What is all this?

58
00:05:29,060 --> 00:05:31,705
What are you doing here?

59
00:05:31,705 --> 00:05:33,647
Get out!

60
00:05:33,647 --> 00:05:35,744
[Episode 2]

61
00:05:37,476 --> 00:05:39,454
Get it together.

62
00:05:39,454 --> 00:05:41,520
Oh my gosh.

63
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:43,621
I haven't even hit you yet.

64
00:05:43,621 --> 00:05:47,752
Ju Yi Jae, you're the problem!

65
00:05:48,416 --> 00:05:49,746
That hurts.

66
00:05:49,746 --> 00:05:53,083
Of course it does. That's why I hit you.

67
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:54,569
Woo Soo Bin!

68
00:05:54,569 --> 00:05:56,022
What about med school?

69
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:59,756
Senior year is crucial. What are you doing?

70
00:05:59,756 --> 00:06:02,076
You're absolutely right.

71
00:06:02,076 --> 00:06:05,334
This shoot is my college exam.

72
00:06:05,334 --> 00:06:09,724
If I win the grand prize,
special admission is a done deal.

73
00:06:09,724 --> 00:06:14,427
Do you even know what that means?

74
00:06:14,427 --> 00:06:15,840
Why are you laughing?

75
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:18,198
Is that so funny?

76
00:06:18,198 --> 00:06:19,708
Listen up.

77
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:21,382
This is a school!

78
00:06:21,382 --> 00:06:24,259
Quit messing around and study!

79
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:25,696
- Yes.
- Yes.

80
00:06:25,696 --> 00:06:28,502
- You okay?
- I'm okay.

81
00:06:29,617 --> 00:06:31,300
Nice accent.

82
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:33,367
You... you okay?

83
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:35,184
That's right.

84
00:06:35,184 --> 00:06:36,627
[Bunam Market]

85
00:06:46,962 --> 00:06:49,027
Let me help you.

86
00:06:55,555 --> 00:06:59,532
Two 5,000-won bags of twist donuts, please.

87
00:06:59,532 --> 00:07:01,962
My mom loves them.

88
00:07:01,962 --> 00:07:03,542
What a good son.

89
00:07:03,542 --> 00:07:05,912
Am I? Aren't you?

90
00:07:05,912 --> 00:07:08,795
No. My mom and I don't get along.

91
00:07:09,451 --> 00:07:11,623
You seemed close to me.

92
00:07:11,623 --> 00:07:14,386
That's just how families are.

93
00:07:17,092 --> 00:07:20,292
- So that's normal?
- Thank you.

94
00:07:31,544 --> 00:07:33,470
Jeez.

95
00:08:04,462 --> 00:08:05,757
She didn't see us, huh?

96
00:08:05,757 --> 00:08:07,152
No.

97
00:08:07,152 --> 00:08:08,737
Come on in.

98
00:08:16,213 --> 00:08:18,613
Ta-da!

99
00:08:18,613 --> 00:08:20,605
What do you think?

100
00:08:20,605 --> 00:08:22,409
Awesome.

101
00:08:23,355 --> 00:08:25,484
[School of Zombie, Ju Yi Jae]

102
00:08:35,370 --> 00:08:36,884
Woo Soo Bin.

103
00:08:36,884 --> 00:08:39,229
Not bad.

104
00:08:43,503 --> 00:08:45,750
Hey, Yi Jae.

105
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:50,080
I want to be a movie director too,
just like you.

106
00:08:51,206 --> 00:08:55,097
If I can't skip med school,
I can just fail to get in.

107
00:08:55,097 --> 00:08:57,278
I'll bomb the college exam.

108
00:08:57,278 --> 00:08:59,825
Then my dad can't force me, yeah?

109
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,724
Woo Soo Bin.

110
00:09:06,724 --> 00:09:10,501
Do you know how hard this path is?

111
00:09:10,501 --> 00:09:13,447
If this is just a phase, forget it.

112
00:09:13,447 --> 00:09:16,373
You've got a long way to go.

113
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:21,385
I've thought about it a lot.

114
00:09:21,385 --> 00:09:23,007
I love movies.

115
00:09:23,007 --> 00:09:25,400
You made me see that.

116
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,795
Me?

117
00:09:27,801 --> 00:09:32,347
The world you see is warm and fun.

118
00:09:33,082 --> 00:09:34,875
It's a zombie movie.

119
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:40,855
Even your zombie world is warm and fun.

120
00:09:42,671 --> 00:09:46,444
I dream of the same world as you.

121
00:09:51,074 --> 00:09:54,586
<i>Woo Soo Bin may never know.</i>

122
00:09:56,878 --> 00:09:58,203
Aren't you leaving?

123
00:09:58,203 --> 00:10:00,659
I'm heading home.

124
00:10:00,659 --> 00:10:04,204
Turn off the lights and lock up later.

125
00:10:05,694 --> 00:10:09,078
What's she doing in there? That's creepy.

126
00:10:09,078 --> 00:10:11,134
She should just study.

127
00:10:34,848 --> 00:10:38,444
<i>Woo Soo Bin may never know.</i>

128
00:10:40,298 --> 00:10:41,944
<i>Yi Jae.</i>

129
00:10:42,789 --> 00:10:44,711
<i>Look good? Acting cool.</i>

130
00:10:44,711 --> 00:10:49,588
<i>The one who brought me
to a warm, joyful world...</i>

131
00:10:51,532 --> 00:10:53,659
<i>was him.</i>

132
00:10:56,819 --> 00:10:57,956
- Soo Bin!
- Yes?

133
00:10:57,956 --> 00:10:59,409
- Aren't you eating?
- No.

134
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:01,203
- Where are you going?
- To celebrate her!

135
00:11:01,203 --> 00:11:04,502
He must be skipping class to see Yi Jae.

136
00:11:20,814 --> 00:11:23,915
Hey, stop!

137
00:11:42,724 --> 00:11:46,152
[2011 Bunam Youth Film Festival, Grand Prize]
I won the grand prize!

138
00:11:49,301 --> 00:11:54,537
[2011 Bunam Youth Film Festival]
My mother once told me to be anyone.

139
00:11:54,537 --> 00:11:58,268
But I don't want to be just anyone.

140
00:11:58,268 --> 00:11:59,700
I was born once!

141
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:01,660
So I'm going to live this life right!

142
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:05,005
I believe people come before movies.

143
00:12:05,005 --> 00:12:08,310
And people come before directors.

144
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:12,282
I will become a film director with heart.

145
00:12:12,282 --> 00:12:14,542
Go, Ju Yi Jae!

146
00:12:18,008 --> 00:12:21,095
What a bold acceptance speech.

147
00:12:21,095 --> 00:12:24,300
Where is her family?

148
00:12:26,857 --> 00:12:29,027
I came alone.

149
00:12:29,027 --> 00:12:32,387
Which is good. No one can take my prize money.

150
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:37,367
Congratulations, Yi Jae.

151
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:46,125
Looks like a close friend came.

152
00:12:49,898 --> 00:12:52,272
Congratulations, Yi Jae.

153
00:13:01,085 --> 00:13:02,629
Woo Soo Bin.

154
00:13:02,629 --> 00:13:05,109
Want to hear a secret?

155
00:13:05,982 --> 00:13:10,273
This is why I wanted to be a film director.

156
00:13:10,273 --> 00:13:11,840
Awards.

157
00:13:13,086 --> 00:13:18,083
I won my first writing award in sixth grade.

158
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:21,660
The way they all looked at me...
I never forgot it.

159
00:13:21,660 --> 00:13:25,459
Looking back,
I think that's where it all started.

160
00:13:26,439 --> 00:13:28,216
Thanks, Soo Bin.

161
00:13:28,216 --> 00:13:30,304
You helped me again.

162
00:13:30,304 --> 00:13:32,209
I didn't do much.

163
00:13:32,209 --> 00:13:35,204
But why is that a secret?

164
00:13:36,024 --> 00:13:40,544
My dream sounds big, but it started so small.

165
00:13:40,544 --> 00:13:45,222
Every great thing starts small.

166
00:13:45,222 --> 00:13:49,876
Like how my feelings for you
became the same dream.

167
00:14:03,277 --> 00:14:06,477
Let's make movies together.

168
00:14:07,770 --> 00:14:09,354
"The Matrix" had two directors.

169
00:14:09,354 --> 00:14:11,776
So did "No Country for Old Men."

170
00:14:15,258 --> 00:14:17,038
What do you think?

171
00:14:17,803 --> 00:14:20,478
- Together?
- Picture this.

172
00:14:20,478 --> 00:14:24,345
Our names, side by side in the credits.

173
00:14:24,345 --> 00:14:27,682
Let's do something great together!

174
00:14:36,312 --> 00:14:38,051
Yeah.

175
00:14:38,051 --> 00:14:40,111
Let's do something great!

176
00:14:40,111 --> 00:14:41,594
Come here.

177
00:14:44,739 --> 00:14:46,433
No, don't do it!

178
00:14:46,433 --> 00:14:47,893
It's cold!

179
00:15:33,913 --> 00:15:35,546
I'm sorry.

180
00:16:01,989 --> 00:16:03,989
I'm home.

181
00:16:20,457 --> 00:16:22,965
In my house,

182
00:16:22,965 --> 00:16:26,569
not one flaw is allowed.

183
00:16:29,058 --> 00:16:31,171
Objects,

184
00:16:32,312 --> 00:16:34,537
plants,

185
00:16:36,017 --> 00:16:38,166
people...

186
00:16:39,430 --> 00:16:41,570
Same rule.

187
00:17:02,252 --> 00:17:04,144
Do you understand?

188
00:17:06,269 --> 00:17:08,521
Yes, Father.

189
00:17:09,849 --> 00:17:10,919
Are these free?

190
00:17:10,919 --> 00:17:13,539
- Isn't this "Memories of Murder?"
- I loved this one.

191
00:17:13,539 --> 00:17:14,976
Right?

192
00:17:14,976 --> 00:17:17,189
Wait. That's mine!

193
00:17:17,189 --> 00:17:18,956
- What?
- That's mine.

194
00:17:18,956 --> 00:17:20,746
What the...

195
00:17:20,746 --> 00:17:22,272
Let's just go.

196
00:17:22,272 --> 00:17:25,704
- What a weirdo.
- Let's go.

197
00:17:25,704 --> 00:17:27,037
[Free: Take Them All!]

198
00:17:34,658 --> 00:17:35,681
Mom!

199
00:17:35,681 --> 00:17:37,537
I'm not deaf, girl.

200
00:17:37,537 --> 00:17:39,748
I told you not to toss these!

201
00:17:39,748 --> 00:17:42,320
Why keep tapes in a noodle shop?

202
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:45,744
- They're not worth a dime.
- What are you talking about?

203
00:17:45,744 --> 00:17:48,847
- They're worth money.
- "Worth money?"

204
00:17:48,847 --> 00:17:51,497
To me, they're dead weight!

205
00:17:51,497 --> 00:17:53,644
I said don't toss them!

206
00:17:53,644 --> 00:17:55,287
I won today!

207
00:17:55,287 --> 00:17:58,014
The prize is one million won.

208
00:17:59,772 --> 00:18:01,189
Good.

209
00:18:01,189 --> 00:18:03,975
Put it toward your dad's gas.

210
00:18:03,975 --> 00:18:07,402
No, I'm putting another table here.

211
00:18:07,402 --> 00:18:10,310
Another table? This place is always dead.

212
00:18:10,310 --> 00:18:12,272
Watch your mouth.

213
00:18:12,272 --> 00:18:15,617
Why? You talk to me like that all the time!

214
00:18:15,617 --> 00:18:18,300
Did I ask for money? Or to study abroad?

215
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:20,646
I don't ask for anything!

216
00:18:20,646 --> 00:18:24,256
Just leave me alone!

217
00:18:24,256 --> 00:18:26,249
God, you're loud.

218
00:18:26,249 --> 00:18:27,540
Fine.

219
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:30,257
Stuff them in storage
or keep them in your room.

220
00:18:30,257 --> 00:18:32,393
Do whatever you want!

221
00:18:48,137 --> 00:18:49,863
Yi Jae.

222
00:19:00,016 --> 00:19:01,662
Were you crying?

223
00:19:01,662 --> 00:19:04,526
Why? What happened?

224
00:19:05,285 --> 00:19:06,990
I'm fine.

225
00:19:06,990 --> 00:19:11,564
Just paying my dues to become a legend.

226
00:19:11,564 --> 00:19:13,114
What?

227
00:19:14,328 --> 00:19:16,532
What are you doing here?

228
00:19:20,308 --> 00:19:22,201
Telepathy?

229
00:19:24,896 --> 00:19:26,993
Woo Soo Bin.

230
00:19:26,993 --> 00:19:30,976
You know The Fox and the Grapes?

231
00:19:30,976 --> 00:19:32,480
What's that?

232
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:36,661
A fox wanted grapes hanging way up high.

233
00:19:36,661 --> 00:19:39,593
He tried everything, but couldn't reach them.

234
00:19:39,593 --> 00:19:42,453
Know what he said?

235
00:19:42,453 --> 00:19:44,093
No idea.

236
00:19:44,762 --> 00:19:46,833
"They're probably sour anyway."

237
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:49,428
Then he gave up.

238
00:19:49,428 --> 00:19:53,697
The fox said it in that accent?

239
00:19:54,357 --> 00:19:57,021
That's not the point.

240
00:19:57,021 --> 00:19:59,865
You're hopeless.

241
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:01,684
Sorry.

242
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:06,238
But maybe they really were sour.

243
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:07,996
So what?

244
00:20:07,996 --> 00:20:11,298
At least he tried them.

245
00:20:11,298 --> 00:20:13,705
If they're bad, spit them out.

246
00:20:13,705 --> 00:20:18,428
You know... Trying beats never trying.

247
00:20:18,428 --> 00:20:22,358
So quitters and finishers are different?

248
00:20:22,358 --> 00:20:23,842
- Right?
- Exactly.

249
00:20:23,842 --> 00:20:25,519
Just watch me.

250
00:20:25,519 --> 00:20:27,262
When I say it, I do it.

251
00:20:27,262 --> 00:20:30,085
Even if it kills me.

252
00:20:30,085 --> 00:20:32,442
Don't let it kill you.

253
00:20:32,442 --> 00:20:34,342
Call me instead.

254
00:20:35,245 --> 00:20:38,769
Wherever you are, I'll come running.

255
00:20:38,769 --> 00:20:41,601
Stand on my shoulders.

256
00:20:57,744 --> 00:21:00,368
<i>I meant every word.</i>

257
00:21:00,368 --> 00:21:03,983
<i>I would've given her everything I had.</i>

258
00:21:08,345 --> 00:21:11,197
[First Short Film - Woo Soo Bin]

259
00:21:12,045 --> 00:21:16,577
<i>After all,
my world was the one she made for me.</i>

260
00:21:42,397 --> 00:21:44,657
[Let's meet at six today. No excuses!]

261
00:22:02,928 --> 00:22:06,689
[Directed/filmed/edited by Woo Soo Bin]

262
00:22:09,616 --> 00:22:11,292
Romance.

263
00:22:15,277 --> 00:22:18,014
Why are you crying?

264
00:22:18,014 --> 00:22:20,615
Let's write a romance together.

265
00:22:20,615 --> 00:22:22,758
An amazing one.

266
00:22:22,758 --> 00:22:23,858
Out of nowhere?

267
00:22:23,858 --> 00:22:25,701
It hit me!

268
00:22:25,701 --> 00:22:26,789
Hey.

269
00:22:26,789 --> 00:22:30,021
Do you know what a director needs most?

270
00:22:30,021 --> 00:22:31,845
Writing is a given.

271
00:22:31,845 --> 00:22:35,738
You need eyes that see the world.

272
00:22:35,738 --> 00:22:37,518
You pass!

273
00:22:38,124 --> 00:22:39,840
Want to kiss?

274
00:22:41,018 --> 00:22:43,276
- What?
- First love. First kiss.

275
00:22:43,276 --> 00:22:45,582
This feels like the scene.

276
00:22:45,582 --> 00:22:47,679
This movie. You.

277
00:22:47,679 --> 00:22:49,579
And this heart.

278
00:22:49,579 --> 00:22:51,872
It feels like now.

279
00:23:09,002 --> 00:23:11,175
Come on.

280
00:23:12,156 --> 00:23:14,896
How can you say that with a straight face?

281
00:23:14,896 --> 00:23:17,926
I'm really nervous now.

282
00:23:19,146 --> 00:23:20,579
Fine.

283
00:23:21,346 --> 00:23:26,617
If we both get into film school,
I'll kiss you first.

284
00:23:26,617 --> 00:23:28,821
How can I wait that long?

285
00:23:31,915 --> 00:23:35,999
If we do it now, I might not stop.

286
00:23:35,999 --> 00:23:37,775
Stop what?

287
00:23:43,708 --> 00:23:48,060
Seniors have a lot to hold back.

288
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:50,199
I'm a senior too.

289
00:23:52,172 --> 00:23:53,603
Right.

290
00:23:53,603 --> 00:23:55,603
Only you're a senior.

291
00:23:58,592 --> 00:24:01,995
Nan Young, a gisaeng with a dream.

292
00:24:01,995 --> 00:24:03,790
But then,

293
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:08,139
as if by fate, a man appeared.

294
00:24:08,139 --> 00:24:10,013
He was shot dead.

295
00:24:10,013 --> 00:24:12,891
How do they fall in love?

296
00:24:12,891 --> 00:24:15,080
Love at first sight?

297
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:17,831
- Did you fall for me at first sight?
- What?

298
00:24:20,928 --> 00:24:22,032
Yeah.

299
00:24:22,032 --> 00:24:24,966
Okay, love at first sight it is.

300
00:24:24,966 --> 00:24:27,321
- Need something cooler.
- A fountain pen?

301
00:24:27,321 --> 00:24:28,356
Or a watch...

302
00:24:28,356 --> 00:24:32,097
Maybe we can make his face stand out.

303
00:24:35,153 --> 00:24:37,511
So he dies in the end?

304
00:24:37,511 --> 00:24:39,510
- Hold on.
- What?

305
00:24:39,510 --> 00:24:42,519
Fine, you're the genius!

306
00:24:44,036 --> 00:24:45,840
Yi Jae...

307
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:47,591
I'm sorry.

308
00:24:51,418 --> 00:24:53,138
Forget it.

309
00:24:53,738 --> 00:24:55,344
How about this?

310
00:25:15,105 --> 00:25:20,222
When you pick grapes, hold them by the bottom.

311
00:25:20,222 --> 00:25:23,919
That way, they won't get damaged.

312
00:25:23,919 --> 00:25:26,059
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

313
00:25:26,059 --> 00:25:29,065
- Hold the bottom like this...
- Firmly.

314
00:25:32,769 --> 00:25:34,959
- Like this?
- That's right.

315
00:25:34,959 --> 00:25:38,340
I raised them like my own kids. No chemicals.

316
00:25:38,340 --> 00:25:40,611
- So treat each one with care.
- Oh, you're here.

317
00:25:40,611 --> 00:25:42,149
- Hello.
- This way.

318
00:25:42,149 --> 00:25:44,049
Thanks for coming.

319
00:25:49,905 --> 00:25:51,180
May I?

320
00:25:51,180 --> 00:25:53,180
Just a second.

321
00:26:09,316 --> 00:26:11,760
Hello, sir.

322
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:13,760
- Welcome.
- Hello.

323
00:26:17,923 --> 00:26:20,008
Hello, Ju Yi Jae.

324
00:26:20,008 --> 00:26:21,848
I'm Ian Woo.

325
00:26:28,113 --> 00:26:30,096
Producer Kyung, what is this?

326
00:26:30,096 --> 00:26:31,216
"This?"

327
00:26:31,216 --> 00:26:32,781
He's today's special guest.

328
00:26:32,781 --> 00:26:34,805
You don't like the flowers?

329
00:26:34,805 --> 00:26:37,163
Since when do we have guests?

330
00:26:37,163 --> 00:26:39,248
- Since today...
- Without a pre-interview?

331
00:26:39,248 --> 00:26:40,558
I'll just pick some grapes.

332
00:26:40,558 --> 00:26:42,388
You're here to become a farmer?

333
00:26:42,388 --> 00:26:43,794
Maybe.

334
00:26:43,794 --> 00:26:45,620
That depends on you.

335
00:26:48,171 --> 00:26:51,135
All right, say hello to...

336
00:26:53,283 --> 00:26:54,720
She must be busy.

337
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:57,389
You even brought flowers?

338
00:26:57,389 --> 00:26:59,393
Thank you.

339
00:26:59,393 --> 00:27:01,113
Beautiful.

340
00:27:05,251 --> 00:27:07,102
I'm a huge fan.

341
00:27:07,102 --> 00:27:08,429
Me too.

342
00:27:08,429 --> 00:27:09,818
Congrats on the award.

343
00:27:09,818 --> 00:27:15,452
I know this was last-minute,
but this feels wrong.

344
00:27:15,452 --> 00:27:18,362
Let's wing it. He's just picking grapes.

345
00:27:18,362 --> 00:27:20,841
Do you know him? You're into movies.

346
00:27:20,841 --> 00:27:23,163
I'd know Bong Joon Ho or Park Chan Wook.

347
00:27:23,163 --> 00:27:24,243
Yeah?

348
00:27:24,243 --> 00:27:27,930
I looked him up,
and it's all about his first love.

349
00:27:27,930 --> 00:27:29,546
Let's dig into that.

350
00:27:29,546 --> 00:27:32,591
A young, handsome director and his love story.

351
00:27:32,591 --> 00:27:37,219
Young, handsome... That's a bit much.

352
00:27:39,124 --> 00:27:42,401
Honestly, he could pass for an actor.

353
00:27:42,401 --> 00:27:46,088
You could be an actor.

354
00:27:46,088 --> 00:27:48,305
That's a stretch.

355
00:27:49,430 --> 00:27:50,581
By the way,

356
00:27:50,581 --> 00:27:53,554
his first love story is already everywhere.

357
00:27:53,554 --> 00:27:56,000
- Do we really need it too?
- Huh?

358
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,381
You said you didn't know him.

359
00:27:59,041 --> 00:28:00,901
Right. I don't.

360
00:28:01,676 --> 00:28:03,653
Can you take a picture of us?

361
00:28:03,653 --> 00:28:06,791
- Look at him. What a hit.
- Thank you.

362
00:28:08,085 --> 00:28:10,834
Please stand over here.

363
00:28:11,492 --> 00:28:13,083
- Here we go.
- Okay.

364
00:28:13,083 --> 00:28:15,392
One, two, cheese.

365
00:28:15,392 --> 00:28:16,802
Finger hearts.

366
00:28:16,802 --> 00:28:18,533
One, two...

367
00:28:18,533 --> 00:28:20,597
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

368
00:28:20,597 --> 00:28:23,141
- We'll go get ready.
- Okay, thank you.

369
00:28:23,141 --> 00:28:25,519
- See you soon.
- Yeah.

370
00:28:30,839 --> 00:28:32,269
What?

371
00:28:35,462 --> 00:28:37,664
Psycho.

372
00:28:37,664 --> 00:28:40,501
- Today, on this farm...
- Ms. Ju Yi Jae.

373
00:28:40,501 --> 00:28:42,226
I look forward to this.

374
00:28:42,226 --> 00:28:46,611
We've never had a surprise guest before.

375
00:28:46,611 --> 00:28:49,648
Please answer each question nicely and clearly.

376
00:28:49,648 --> 00:28:52,202
Talking back is your specialty, huh?

377
00:28:52,202 --> 00:28:54,352
Producer Kyung has the flowers.

378
00:28:54,352 --> 00:28:56,094
Make sure you take them.

379
00:28:56,094 --> 00:28:58,481
You never revealed your real name anywhere.

380
00:28:58,481 --> 00:29:00,811
Must be a lot you're hiding.

381
00:29:00,811 --> 00:29:02,886
Was that on the card?

382
00:29:02,886 --> 00:29:05,366
Yeah, that was personal.

383
00:29:05,366 --> 00:29:07,390
Your real name is Woo Soo Bin. Next.

384
00:29:07,390 --> 00:29:09,206
What are your future plans?

385
00:29:09,206 --> 00:29:11,690
Why did you come on our show?

386
00:29:11,690 --> 00:29:13,196
Oh, right.

387
00:29:13,196 --> 00:29:15,276
Why are you here?

388
00:29:20,015 --> 00:29:21,734
To see you.

389
00:29:22,328 --> 00:29:25,685
When did this start?

390
00:29:25,685 --> 00:29:27,855
The station?

391
00:29:27,855 --> 00:29:29,879
The online deal?

392
00:29:29,879 --> 00:29:31,249
From here...

393
00:29:31,249 --> 00:29:33,697
What are you doing?

394
00:29:35,372 --> 00:29:37,024
I pulled a few strings.

395
00:29:37,024 --> 00:29:38,902
And the online deal?

396
00:29:38,902 --> 00:29:40,876
I heard Yu Geon talking to you.

397
00:29:40,876 --> 00:29:42,638
Yu Geon, that little...

398
00:29:42,638 --> 00:29:44,554
That's a lot of questions.

399
00:29:44,554 --> 00:29:47,759
Are you curious too?

400
00:29:47,759 --> 00:29:49,310
I'll answer everything.

401
00:29:49,310 --> 00:29:51,908
Even about my first love, if you want.

402
00:29:51,908 --> 00:29:53,173
You little...

403
00:29:53,173 --> 00:29:55,525
I'm kidding.

404
00:29:55,525 --> 00:29:57,816
- You looked too nervous.
- Come on.

405
00:29:57,816 --> 00:29:59,186
Who says I'm nervous?

406
00:29:59,186 --> 00:30:02,525
You keep biting your lip.

407
00:30:02,525 --> 00:30:04,469
That's your tell.

408
00:30:04,469 --> 00:30:06,371
You'll make it bleed.

409
00:30:08,567 --> 00:30:11,363
Hey. Woo Soo Bin.

410
00:30:11,363 --> 00:30:14,466
- Yeah?
- Try anything...

411
00:30:24,221 --> 00:30:25,972
Stand by.

412
00:30:25,972 --> 00:30:27,707
Cue!

413
00:30:27,707 --> 00:30:29,371
Hello, viewers!

414
00:30:29,371 --> 00:30:31,687
I'm Ju Yi Jae of Here Comes Yi Jae.

415
00:30:31,687 --> 00:30:37,234
We go wherever you are, all across the country.

416
00:30:37,234 --> 00:30:40,917
So where am I today?

417
00:30:40,917 --> 00:30:44,655
This sun, this breeze, this perfect weather...

418
00:30:44,655 --> 00:30:46,495
Can you feel it?

419
00:30:47,864 --> 00:30:50,288
And that fresh scent of grapes.

420
00:30:52,483 --> 00:30:54,628
She's really good.

421
00:30:54,628 --> 00:30:56,420
Sorry?

422
00:30:56,420 --> 00:30:58,588
- Please stand by.
- Got it.

423
00:30:58,588 --> 00:31:03,902
A major event in European cinema,
the European International Film Awards.

424
00:31:03,902 --> 00:31:05,199
He won two awards there.

425
00:31:05,199 --> 00:31:07,306
Please welcome Director Ian Woo!

426
00:31:07,306 --> 00:31:09,885
Hello, Director.

427
00:31:09,885 --> 00:31:11,310
Hello.

428
00:31:11,310 --> 00:31:13,353
I'm Ian Woo, a filmmaker.

429
00:31:13,353 --> 00:31:18,284
It's an honor to be on this show.

430
00:31:18,284 --> 00:31:21,953
Can we count on you today?

431
00:31:21,953 --> 00:31:24,210
I'll do my best.

432
00:31:24,210 --> 00:31:26,949
Let's do this!

433
00:31:28,159 --> 00:31:31,875
- Looking forward to today.
- Same here.

434
00:31:32,466 --> 00:31:34,252
Cut!

435
00:31:39,329 --> 00:31:41,619
Is she always like that?

436
00:31:41,619 --> 00:31:43,035
Well...

437
00:31:45,745 --> 00:31:51,390
What does "Wandering," the film that
brought you a major award, mean to you?

438
00:31:51,390 --> 00:31:55,132
It's special because it's my first feature.

439
00:31:55,132 --> 00:31:56,837
But I think

440
00:31:56,837 --> 00:32:00,670
it's even more precious to me
because it gave me a second chance.

441
00:32:00,670 --> 00:32:03,183
What do you mean by that?

442
00:32:04,163 --> 00:32:08,534
If I'm nobody, who would care about my story?

443
00:32:08,534 --> 00:32:11,178
I had to become a director first
if I wanted to do what I wanted.

444
00:32:11,178 --> 00:32:16,147
So "Wandering" was made with that calculation

445
00:32:16,147 --> 00:32:17,785
in mind.

446
00:32:19,392 --> 00:32:21,017
Did that sound too full of myself?

447
00:32:21,017 --> 00:32:25,129
No. It sounded very realistic.

448
00:32:25,129 --> 00:32:30,556
From a distance,
the world of film seems so romantic.

449
00:32:30,556 --> 00:32:34,126
Now I'm preparing my next film
for that romance.

450
00:32:34,126 --> 00:32:36,546
That's why I came back to Korea.

451
00:32:37,855 --> 00:32:39,706
The title is

452
00:32:40,522 --> 00:32:42,419
"Gyeongseong Love Song."

453
00:32:54,236 --> 00:32:55,396
[Sim Yu Geon]

454
00:33:00,357 --> 00:33:03,504
If you told me to die, I would.

455
00:33:04,163 --> 00:33:07,943
- Here's my profile.
- It's already right there.

456
00:33:07,943 --> 00:33:10,354
He still likes you when your ramyeon sucks?

457
00:33:10,354 --> 00:33:12,709
That's true love.

458
00:33:19,602 --> 00:33:20,856
[Profile submissions closed]

459
00:33:37,307 --> 00:33:39,051
Hey!

460
00:33:39,051 --> 00:33:40,989
What took you so long?

461
00:33:40,989 --> 00:33:42,489
I'm not the delivery.

462
00:33:42,489 --> 00:33:44,961
Huh? I'll call you back.

463
00:33:44,961 --> 00:33:46,681
What did you say?

464
00:33:51,569 --> 00:33:53,521
Hi, Team Lead Kang.

465
00:33:53,521 --> 00:33:55,767
It's me, Sim Yu Geon.

466
00:33:55,767 --> 00:33:57,511
Sim Yu Geon?

467
00:33:57,511 --> 00:33:59,933
Here's my profile.

468
00:34:01,519 --> 00:34:04,322
So you moved here.

469
00:34:04,945 --> 00:34:07,083
You don't remember me?

470
00:34:07,083 --> 00:34:09,663
You were with Actor Team Three.

471
00:34:09,663 --> 00:34:11,406
It's been a while.

472
00:34:11,406 --> 00:34:13,475
- How have you been?
- Fine.

473
00:34:13,475 --> 00:34:17,031
And it's Director now.

474
00:34:17,830 --> 00:34:20,856
You kept yourself up.

475
00:34:21,850 --> 00:34:24,480
That was five, six years ago...

476
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:28,630
You must be around 30 now.

477
00:34:28,630 --> 00:34:32,134
- I turn 30 next year.
- Yeah, right.

478
00:34:32,134 --> 00:34:33,804
Did you serve?

479
00:34:33,804 --> 00:34:37,269
Yes. Right after I left the company.

480
00:34:38,286 --> 00:34:40,977
"Left the company?"

481
00:34:42,149 --> 00:34:45,607
The CEO scammed us,
and the company vanished overnight.

482
00:34:45,607 --> 00:34:48,248
What a nice way to put it.

483
00:34:48,879 --> 00:34:51,536
You're too nice.

484
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:56,023
Well...

485
00:34:56,023 --> 00:34:58,668
It's all in the past now.

486
00:34:58,668 --> 00:35:00,688
Gosh.

487
00:35:00,688 --> 00:35:03,000
That's why you're failing.

488
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,251
I can tell just by looking.

489
00:35:04,251 --> 00:35:07,216
Whether someone will make it or not.

490
00:35:07,216 --> 00:35:09,666
Anyway, Yu Geon.

491
00:35:09,666 --> 00:35:12,256
You're not young. Move on.

492
00:35:12,256 --> 00:35:16,094
I'm saying this for your own good.

493
00:35:16,094 --> 00:35:21,862
We were once at the same agency.
So I do feel bad.

494
00:35:21,862 --> 00:35:23,473
There it is.

495
00:35:23,473 --> 00:35:24,963
Bye.

496
00:35:25,562 --> 00:35:28,813
- What took you so long?
- Sorry.

497
00:35:29,949 --> 00:35:31,750
Remember that.

498
00:35:53,606 --> 00:35:56,823
- Sure.
- Ma'am, your lunch is here.

499
00:35:56,823 --> 00:35:58,754
Ha Na loves the script.

500
00:35:58,754 --> 00:36:00,975
She's dying to do it.

501
00:36:00,975 --> 00:36:04,221
Her shoot wraps soon. She can start right away.

502
00:36:04,901 --> 00:36:08,033
Of course. Bye.

503
00:36:11,368 --> 00:36:13,838
Since when am I dying to do it?

504
00:36:13,838 --> 00:36:15,090
Looks good.

505
00:36:15,090 --> 00:36:18,255
Then again, do I ever get a choice?

506
00:36:18,255 --> 00:36:20,145
Not for you.

507
00:36:20,145 --> 00:36:22,033
You have a dress to fit into.

508
00:36:22,033 --> 00:36:23,573
Skip it.

509
00:36:24,455 --> 00:36:28,132
I had to delay that scene
while you lost weight.

510
00:36:28,132 --> 00:36:31,328
Then change the dress!

511
00:36:31,328 --> 00:36:33,702
I'm taking a break after this.

512
00:36:33,702 --> 00:36:35,750
Don't send me scripts.

513
00:36:36,408 --> 00:36:39,932
You think scripts just come to you?

514
00:36:39,932 --> 00:36:41,576
An actress's career is short.

515
00:36:41,576 --> 00:36:43,934
One day, the world will move on.

516
00:36:43,934 --> 00:36:45,686
Don't rest now.

517
00:36:45,686 --> 00:36:47,676
Then when do I rest?

518
00:36:47,676 --> 00:36:50,063
- After I get married like you?
- Yes.

519
00:36:50,063 --> 00:36:53,200
Then use your kid for a comeback.

520
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:54,504
Hey.

521
00:36:54,504 --> 00:36:56,603
Be proud.

522
00:36:57,253 --> 00:36:59,883
She started the parenting-show craze.

523
00:36:59,883 --> 00:37:01,277
I see.

524
00:37:01,277 --> 00:37:03,901
Don't forget that.

525
00:37:03,901 --> 00:37:05,952
That was my popularity.

526
00:37:05,952 --> 00:37:08,967
- Right.
- I made it happen.

527
00:37:08,967 --> 00:37:11,443
I'm going to the salon.

528
00:37:12,067 --> 00:37:13,551
Sorry?

529
00:37:13,551 --> 00:37:14,675
Already?

530
00:37:14,675 --> 00:37:16,965
We still have time. Let me eat...

531
00:37:16,965 --> 00:37:18,722
Let's go.

532
00:37:22,404 --> 00:37:24,522
- Keep her hair down.
- Got it.

533
00:37:24,522 --> 00:37:27,305
Ha Na, wait!

534
00:37:29,313 --> 00:37:34,484
Welcome to the press event for
"10 Reasons Contract Marriage Is Dangerous."

535
00:37:34,484 --> 00:37:38,447
First, please welcome Oh Ha Na,
who plays Lee Yoon A.

536
00:37:38,447 --> 00:37:40,681
Now for photo time.

537
00:37:40,681 --> 00:37:41,807
[Press Event]

538
00:37:46,194 --> 00:37:48,752
They look amazing.

539
00:37:48,752 --> 00:37:51,032
A heart with the director... Great.

540
00:37:51,032 --> 00:37:53,005
I have a question for Oh Ha Na.

541
00:37:53,005 --> 00:37:56,911
Your mother, CEO An Su Hui,
was also an actress.

542
00:37:56,911 --> 00:38:00,443
What advice did she give you this time?

543
00:38:01,747 --> 00:38:04,128
She always gives me plenty of advice

544
00:38:04,128 --> 00:38:08,022
as a strict senior and a reliable CEO.

545
00:38:08,022 --> 00:38:11,088
But this time...

546
00:38:11,088 --> 00:38:16,404
She talked more about
why marriage is dangerous.

547
00:38:18,030 --> 00:38:19,340
I see.

548
00:38:19,340 --> 00:38:23,943
How was your chemistry with Ha Na
as a married couple?

549
00:38:25,689 --> 00:38:28,453
I guess

550
00:38:28,453 --> 00:38:32,944
since Ha Na has never dated...
she didn't really get it.

551
00:38:34,549 --> 00:38:37,955
I never said I've never dated.

552
00:38:37,955 --> 00:38:41,772
She debuted over 20 years ago
and never had one dating rumor.

553
00:38:41,772 --> 00:38:43,804
That says it all.

554
00:38:43,804 --> 00:38:45,825
Am I wrong?

555
00:38:51,639 --> 00:38:54,232
Do you like me?

556
00:38:54,232 --> 00:38:56,017
What?

557
00:38:57,198 --> 00:39:01,122
Their back-and-forth
already feels like a drama scene.

558
00:39:01,122 --> 00:39:04,260
This makes us even more excited.

559
00:39:04,260 --> 00:39:05,406
Then shall we...

560
00:39:05,406 --> 00:39:07,849
What? "Do you like me?"

561
00:39:07,849 --> 00:39:11,293
What man would like that temper?

562
00:39:11,293 --> 00:39:13,748
Hey.

563
00:39:13,748 --> 00:39:17,220
I let her name go first.
And I entered after her too?

564
00:39:17,220 --> 00:39:18,286
That's too much.

565
00:39:18,286 --> 00:39:19,427
Well...

566
00:39:19,427 --> 00:39:22,827
The company will paint you as a gentleman.

567
00:39:22,827 --> 00:39:26,444
That hurts my pride. Darn it.

568
00:39:26,444 --> 00:39:28,334
How much does she make per episode?

569
00:39:28,334 --> 00:39:30,628
Don't tell me she makes more too.

570
00:39:30,628 --> 00:39:31,898
Of course not.

571
00:39:31,898 --> 00:39:34,218
You're the male lead.

572
00:39:34,218 --> 00:39:36,555
Without her mom, she's nothing.

573
00:39:36,555 --> 00:39:38,848
And I'm supposed to bow to her?

574
00:39:38,848 --> 00:39:41,320
Everyone knows she's Mommy's little girl.

575
00:39:41,320 --> 00:39:43,591
Even my neighbor's dog knows.

576
00:39:43,591 --> 00:39:45,073
Just close the door.

577
00:39:45,073 --> 00:39:47,056
Mommy!

578
00:39:47,056 --> 00:39:49,429
I'm so upset right now.

579
00:39:49,429 --> 00:39:52,407
That jerk Go Sang Yeon
called me Mommy's little girl!

580
00:39:52,407 --> 00:39:54,699
- Please yell at him.
- CEO An!

581
00:39:54,699 --> 00:39:57,311
That's not what I meant...

582
00:39:57,311 --> 00:39:59,831
Darn it.

583
00:40:00,488 --> 00:40:03,214
Are you insane? What are you doing?

584
00:40:03,214 --> 00:40:05,344
Yes. I'm insane.

585
00:40:05,344 --> 00:40:09,447
You're scared of my mom, idiot.

586
00:40:12,753 --> 00:40:14,697
Hey, get over here.

587
00:40:14,697 --> 00:40:17,064
I said get over here!

588
00:40:17,064 --> 00:40:18,361
- Let's just go.
- Hey!

589
00:40:18,361 --> 00:40:20,095
You little...

590
00:40:20,095 --> 00:40:21,887
Get over here!

591
00:40:22,659 --> 00:40:24,722
<i>Okay, drone shot is next.</i>

592
00:40:24,722 --> 00:40:29,490
<i>We're cleared to ride, so we'll take the truck.</i>

593
00:40:41,034 --> 00:40:43,860
You know The Fox and the Grapes?

594
00:40:45,012 --> 00:40:49,730
A fox tried to reach some grapes,
but he couldn't.

595
00:40:49,730 --> 00:40:52,592
So what did he do?

596
00:40:53,303 --> 00:40:54,481
Not sure.

597
00:40:54,481 --> 00:40:56,679
"They're probably sour anyway."

598
00:40:56,679 --> 00:40:58,669
"Good thing I didn't eat them."

599
00:40:58,669 --> 00:41:00,963
He rationalized it.

600
00:41:00,963 --> 00:41:03,400
Maybe they really were sour.

601
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:06,420
You never know until you try.

602
00:41:06,420 --> 00:41:09,124
Sadly, the fox will never know.

603
00:41:09,124 --> 00:41:11,857
All that time for one grape?

604
00:41:11,857 --> 00:41:15,518
Not if he got it. But he didn't.

605
00:41:15,518 --> 00:41:17,002
He climbed the tree.

606
00:41:17,002 --> 00:41:20,335
He even used a ladder,
but still couldn't reach.

607
00:41:20,335 --> 00:41:22,752
He hurt his hand. He hurt his leg.

608
00:41:22,752 --> 00:41:25,481
Someone even kicked the ladder away.

609
00:41:25,481 --> 00:41:27,211
And he still shouldn't quit?

610
00:41:27,211 --> 00:41:29,731
What if a friend came to help?

611
00:41:32,263 --> 00:41:36,686
If he stepped on that friend's back,
he could reach them.

612
00:41:36,686 --> 00:41:39,504
<i>Stand on my shoulders.</i>

613
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:45,073
That friend might snatch them first.

614
00:41:45,073 --> 00:41:48,959
Then he wasted his time and got hurt.

615
00:41:49,737 --> 00:41:52,224
- Yi Jae. You think I took it?
- Are you crazy?

616
00:41:52,224 --> 00:41:54,524
The mic is on.

617
00:41:57,499 --> 00:41:58,670
<i>What's going on?</i>

618
00:41:58,670 --> 00:42:01,698
<i>Why grab his collar?</i>

619
00:42:04,864 --> 00:42:07,434
His shirt button came off!

620
00:42:07,434 --> 00:42:11,145
Must be the wind. That scared me.

621
00:42:13,085 --> 00:42:15,549
<i>Are you okay, sir?</i>

622
00:42:15,549 --> 00:42:19,968
Buttons are falling like leaves.

623
00:42:19,968 --> 00:42:22,194
Must be autumn.

624
00:42:22,194 --> 00:42:24,078
He must be flustered too.

625
00:42:24,078 --> 00:42:26,507
He's just saying anything.

626
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:29,158
Ju Yi Jae!

627
00:42:29,158 --> 00:42:32,285
- Sew it on when you get off.
- Okay.

628
00:42:32,285 --> 00:42:34,538
That scared me.

629
00:43:03,368 --> 00:43:05,392
Thirty million.

630
00:43:05,392 --> 00:43:08,638
- What?
- For the script. I'll sell it.

631
00:43:08,638 --> 00:43:11,504
You need my okay to make it.

632
00:43:13,378 --> 00:43:16,508
I want to finish this story with you.

633
00:43:16,508 --> 00:43:19,191
If you won't, it means nothing to me.

634
00:43:19,191 --> 00:43:21,388
It's just old pages.

635
00:43:21,388 --> 00:43:22,774
Yeah?

636
00:43:22,774 --> 00:43:24,091
Then burn it.

637
00:43:24,091 --> 00:43:26,212
I don't care.

638
00:43:27,659 --> 00:43:29,901
You said I stole it.

639
00:43:31,075 --> 00:43:33,239
You said I was your regret.

640
00:43:34,269 --> 00:43:37,239
I don't want to be that to you.

641
00:43:37,239 --> 00:43:39,922
That's why I can't give up.

642
00:43:55,313 --> 00:43:59,896
I'll return the dream I stole from you.

643
00:43:59,896 --> 00:44:02,327
Even your first love, if you want.

644
00:44:06,026 --> 00:44:10,093
How do I give that back?

645
00:44:15,799 --> 00:44:17,582
What do I do?

646
00:44:23,877 --> 00:44:25,548
Should I?

647
00:44:29,959 --> 00:44:32,292
We're not in high school anymore.

648
00:44:33,430 --> 00:44:35,430
No reason to hold back.

649
00:44:47,250 --> 00:44:49,327
You bastard.

650
00:45:00,363 --> 00:45:02,151
Woo Soo Bin!

651
00:45:03,433 --> 00:45:05,516
Woo Soo Bin!

652
00:45:32,767 --> 00:45:34,922
I'm leaving!

653
00:45:55,667 --> 00:45:58,553
The lights are on...

654
00:46:34,361 --> 00:46:36,347
Thank God.

655
00:46:38,359 --> 00:46:40,080
Why are you skipping school?

656
00:46:40,080 --> 00:46:42,613
Why won't you answer my calls?

657
00:46:42,613 --> 00:46:45,773
Our film school exam is tomorrow.

658
00:46:45,773 --> 00:46:48,012
I'm not going.

659
00:46:49,186 --> 00:46:50,936
You go alone.

660
00:46:50,936 --> 00:46:53,111
I came out to tell you that.

661
00:46:53,111 --> 00:46:54,530
Why?

662
00:46:55,156 --> 00:46:57,668
I'm going to America.

663
00:46:57,668 --> 00:47:00,317
I have to become a doctor.

664
00:47:00,317 --> 00:47:03,134
But you don't want to be a doctor.

665
00:47:04,132 --> 00:47:06,035
What does that matter?

666
00:47:10,086 --> 00:47:11,513
You should go.

667
00:47:22,175 --> 00:47:26,506
Look. We wrote all this.
It doesn't even have an ending.

668
00:47:26,506 --> 00:47:28,802
You can't just leave.

669
00:47:28,802 --> 00:47:30,936
You wanted to direct movies too.

670
00:47:30,936 --> 00:47:33,614
You said you found a dream.

671
00:47:36,712 --> 00:47:40,671
It was just a passing dream.

672
00:47:41,887 --> 00:47:44,273
It was never going to happen.

673
00:47:45,913 --> 00:47:47,941
That's a lie.

674
00:47:47,941 --> 00:47:49,483
That's a lie.

675
00:47:49,483 --> 00:47:51,487
It's not true.

676
00:47:51,487 --> 00:47:53,711
You don't want to go to America!

677
00:47:53,711 --> 00:47:54,896
You promised!

678
00:47:54,896 --> 00:47:57,425
We'd make movies together!

679
00:47:59,664 --> 00:48:02,041
You promised...

680
00:48:19,418 --> 00:48:20,584
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

681
00:48:21,691 --> 00:48:23,855
Then you take this.

682
00:48:23,855 --> 00:48:26,355
You know what this means.

683
00:48:26,355 --> 00:48:28,292
You choose.

684
00:48:28,292 --> 00:48:30,292
I'll be waiting.

685
00:48:31,700 --> 00:48:33,191
Yi Jae.

686
00:48:33,959 --> 00:48:35,765
Ju Yi Jae!

687
00:48:40,023 --> 00:48:43,451
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

688
00:48:45,745 --> 00:48:47,647
[Express Bus: Seoul-Bunam]

689
00:48:50,702 --> 00:48:52,860
[Bus Ticket]
[From Bunam to Seoul]

690
00:49:02,679 --> 00:49:05,251
The bus is leaving now.

691
00:49:19,907 --> 00:49:22,923
Wait! I need to get off!

692
00:50:30,799 --> 00:50:32,656
[Operating Room]

693
00:50:37,797 --> 00:50:39,723
Honey...

694
00:50:44,784 --> 00:50:47,162
What do we do?

695
00:50:47,162 --> 00:50:49,208
My daughter...

696
00:51:39,199 --> 00:51:42,440
Ms. Ju Yi Jae! Can you hear me?

697
00:51:42,440 --> 00:51:45,872
Room 310, she is awake.

698
00:51:45,872 --> 00:51:48,366
- Yi Jae!
- Yi Jae!

699
00:51:49,425 --> 00:51:51,466
Are you awake?

700
00:51:51,466 --> 00:51:52,557
You okay?

701
00:51:52,557 --> 00:51:54,632
Do you recognize me?

702
00:51:55,702 --> 00:51:58,406
Why are you dressed like that?

703
00:51:58,406 --> 00:52:00,889
I'm not dead yet.

704
00:52:00,889 --> 00:52:05,922
Yi Jae...

705
00:52:05,922 --> 00:52:08,844
Yi Jae...

706
00:52:13,387 --> 00:52:14,726
Yi Jae.

707
00:52:15,477 --> 00:52:19,213
Your dad must've woken you before he left.

708
00:52:45,313 --> 00:52:48,278
<i>A life touched by regret</i>

709
00:52:48,278 --> 00:52:52,438
<i>can fall apart at any moment.</i>

710
00:53:04,241 --> 00:53:07,818
<i>You know The Fox and the Grapes?</i>

711
00:53:07,818 --> 00:53:11,635
<i>A fox wanted grapes hanging way up high.</i>

712
00:53:11,635 --> 00:53:14,652
<i>He tried everything, but couldn't reach them.</i>

713
00:53:14,652 --> 00:53:17,045
<i>Call me instead.</i>

714
00:53:17,045 --> 00:53:19,304
<i>Wherever you are, I'll come running.</i>

715
00:53:21,518 --> 00:53:24,274
<i>Stand on my shoulders.</i>

716
00:53:38,105 --> 00:53:40,204
<i>My regret...</i>

717
00:53:42,814 --> 00:53:44,555
<i>was me all along.</i>

718
00:54:07,798 --> 00:54:09,787
<i>You bastard.</i>

719
00:54:14,311 --> 00:54:16,651
God, I'm an idiot.

720
00:54:22,219 --> 00:54:24,383
[Jaejae Noodles]
<i>I'm Ian Woo, a filmmaker.</i>

721
00:54:24,383 --> 00:54:26,396
<i>- It's an honor to be on this show.</i>
- Mom!

722
00:54:26,396 --> 00:54:27,453
Mom!

723
00:54:27,453 --> 00:54:29,080
Mom!

724
00:54:29,080 --> 00:54:30,951
- Look at this!
- What?

725
00:54:30,951 --> 00:54:32,010
Look at the TV!

726
00:54:32,010 --> 00:54:35,438
<i>You fell while digging clams on the mudflats.</i>

727
00:54:35,438 --> 00:54:39,724
Isn't that Soo Bin with Yi Jae?

728
00:54:42,171 --> 00:54:47,100
<i>That's what gets our viewers laughing.</i>

729
00:54:47,100 --> 00:54:48,996
What the heck?

730
00:54:48,996 --> 00:54:51,304
Why is he on that show?

731
00:55:07,048 --> 00:55:09,413
Why say no? That's what's weird.

732
00:55:09,413 --> 00:55:11,313
Why should I say yes?

733
00:55:11,313 --> 00:55:15,425
You said dreams aren't first-come,
first-served.

734
00:55:15,425 --> 00:55:16,891
Maybe yours just took longer.

735
00:55:16,891 --> 00:55:20,791
I'm not young anymore. I can't live on dreams.

736
00:55:20,791 --> 00:55:23,067
That's insane.

737
00:55:23,067 --> 00:55:24,478
What about me?

738
00:55:24,478 --> 00:55:26,945
Hey, you're different.

739
00:55:26,945 --> 00:55:29,955
Your dream's still alive. Mine is over.

740
00:55:29,955 --> 00:55:33,525
And your dad might back you up.

741
00:55:33,525 --> 00:55:35,342
You have it easier.

742
00:55:35,342 --> 00:55:36,965
Excuses.

743
00:55:37,984 --> 00:55:42,342
So I'm only doing this
because I have a safety net?

744
00:55:42,342 --> 00:55:44,588
That's not what I meant.

745
00:55:47,401 --> 00:55:48,685
I'm sorry.

746
00:55:48,685 --> 00:55:51,587
I was out of line.

747
00:55:52,892 --> 00:55:56,636
Passing up a chance... that's what's insane.

748
00:55:56,636 --> 00:55:58,493
You've done it before.

749
00:55:58,493 --> 00:56:01,419
I guess Soo Bin is here to make it up to you.

750
00:56:01,419 --> 00:56:04,490
- Think of it that way.
- He didn't take it. I let it go.

751
00:56:04,490 --> 00:56:06,863
You gave up the exam and ran after him...

752
00:56:06,863 --> 00:56:08,650
Sim Yu Geon.

753
00:56:12,257 --> 00:56:14,680
And look how you lived after that.

754
00:56:14,680 --> 00:56:17,626
Don't those years feel wasted?

755
00:56:18,613 --> 00:56:21,957
Value yourself a little.

756
00:56:21,957 --> 00:56:24,458
Stop calling yourself pathetic.

757
00:56:28,527 --> 00:56:30,860
Where are you going?

758
00:56:30,860 --> 00:56:33,066
To make a living.

759
00:56:34,540 --> 00:56:37,111
- I'm here for my shift.
- Start with the dishes.

760
00:56:37,111 --> 00:56:38,620
Yes, sir.

761
00:56:47,718 --> 00:56:49,473
[Here Comes Yi Jae]
[Viewer Board]

762
00:56:49,473 --> 00:56:52,800
"Woo Fox picked my heart, not grapes."

763
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:57,521
"Ian Woo, you're dangerously perfect."

764
00:56:57,521 --> 00:56:59,529
What is happening?

765
00:56:59,529 --> 00:57:01,328
Yes!

766
00:57:01,985 --> 00:57:04,505
We got it! Hold on...

767
00:57:04,505 --> 00:57:05,535
Yeah, CP.

768
00:57:05,535 --> 00:57:07,701
Are you at your desk?

769
00:57:08,683 --> 00:57:11,254
Gosh. You washed up here again?

770
00:57:11,254 --> 00:57:13,168
Is this overtime or a sleepover?

771
00:57:13,168 --> 00:57:14,838
A sleepover.

772
00:57:14,838 --> 00:57:17,944
Hey, that's not important.

773
00:57:17,944 --> 00:57:20,962
When was the last time you blew up like this?

774
00:57:20,962 --> 00:57:23,155
Never.

775
00:57:23,155 --> 00:57:25,300
I've never seen high schoolers watch my show.

776
00:57:25,300 --> 00:57:30,439
I know.
His clips were all over our team chat today.

777
00:57:31,873 --> 00:57:33,340
What?

778
00:57:33,340 --> 00:57:37,090
But... Isn't Woo Soo Bin that guy?

779
00:57:37,090 --> 00:57:38,963
Your first love?

780
00:57:39,869 --> 00:57:41,400
What did he say?

781
00:57:41,400 --> 00:57:43,507
Did he miss you? Still love you?

782
00:57:43,507 --> 00:57:45,324
What are you talking about?

783
00:57:45,324 --> 00:57:47,984
A first-love reunion?

784
00:57:48,690 --> 00:57:50,714
You know I love those!

785
00:57:50,714 --> 00:57:52,745
Hey, I have to go.

786
00:57:52,745 --> 00:57:54,371
Lay off the romance novels.

787
00:57:54,371 --> 00:57:56,786
Don't tell anyone.

788
00:57:56,786 --> 00:58:00,307
- Hello, sir?
- Now I'm hooked.

789
00:58:00,307 --> 00:58:02,697
Right. Work.

790
00:58:08,329 --> 00:58:10,661
Yeah, come in.

791
00:58:13,101 --> 00:58:15,126
- Hey.
- You're here.

792
00:58:15,126 --> 00:58:16,410
Sit.

793
00:58:16,410 --> 00:58:18,731
What's this?

794
00:58:18,731 --> 00:58:20,163
Beer in broad daylight?

795
00:58:20,163 --> 00:58:21,864
Trying to butter me up?

796
00:58:21,864 --> 00:58:23,702
A chicken bribe?

797
00:58:25,736 --> 00:58:27,360
It's crispy.

798
00:58:27,360 --> 00:58:29,124
Well...

799
00:58:29,124 --> 00:58:32,401
You know that director, don't you?

800
00:58:34,199 --> 00:58:35,210
What?

801
00:58:35,210 --> 00:58:38,215
- Yeah?
- No, I don't.

802
00:58:38,215 --> 00:58:41,305
- What director?
- You think I'm clueless, right?

803
00:58:41,305 --> 00:58:42,615
Hey.

804
00:58:42,615 --> 00:58:47,085
I watched you two for hours in the edit room.

805
00:58:49,142 --> 00:58:50,379
Yeah...

806
00:58:50,379 --> 00:58:53,225
We went to school together.
We're not exactly close.

807
00:58:54,056 --> 00:58:57,267
Perfect. Get him back on the show.

808
00:58:57,267 --> 00:58:59,061
What? No way.

809
00:58:59,061 --> 00:59:01,809
- Repeats aren't fun.
- Come on.

810
00:59:01,809 --> 00:59:03,659
Don't be dense.

811
00:59:03,659 --> 00:59:05,399
Let's ride this.

812
00:59:05,399 --> 00:59:07,116
Before another show grabs him.

813
00:59:07,116 --> 00:59:09,988
- Don't hand him over.
- Let them have him.

814
00:59:09,988 --> 00:59:13,192
This season has fall leaves,
harvests, and plenty to cover.

815
00:59:13,192 --> 00:59:15,276
Are we just worshipping some director?

816
00:59:15,276 --> 00:59:17,653
Let's go plan the next item.

817
00:59:17,653 --> 00:59:20,459
If this works, we get our own slot.

818
00:59:20,459 --> 00:59:23,893
This is our big chance.

819
00:59:23,893 --> 00:59:25,031
<i>Ju Yi Jae.</i>

820
00:59:25,031 --> 00:59:27,371
<i>Bring him back, no matter what.</i>

821
00:59:27,371 --> 00:59:29,635
<i>Fail, and don't come back to Seoul.</i>

822
00:59:29,635 --> 00:59:32,568
<i>He's somewhere in Bunam right now.</i>

823
00:59:32,568 --> 00:59:34,890
<i>Book him. No excuses.</i>

824
00:59:49,983 --> 00:59:52,447
[Welcome to Bunam City]

825
01:00:50,660 --> 01:00:52,606
Excuse me.

826
01:01:56,088 --> 01:01:57,246
<i>Hit me.</i>

827
01:01:57,246 --> 01:01:58,359
<i>I had hope...</i>

828
01:01:58,359 --> 01:02:00,143
<i>How much will you tell me?</i>

829
01:02:00,143 --> 01:02:03,203
<i>I'll tell you everything I know.</i>

830
01:02:03,203 --> 01:02:04,380
<i>Who are you?</i>

831
01:02:04,380 --> 01:02:05,780
<i>I keep thinking about you.</i>

832
01:02:05,780 --> 01:02:08,293
<i>Want to be my friend?</i>

833
01:02:08,293 --> 01:02:11,703
<i>I'm not asking for understanding
or forgiveness now.</i>

834
01:02:11,703 --> 01:02:14,103
<i>You jerk. Why keep following me?</i>

835
01:02:14,103 --> 01:02:16,540
<i>I never forgot you.</i>

836
01:02:16,540 --> 01:02:19,224
<i>Why am I here?</i>

837
01:02:19,224 --> 01:02:22,544
<i>You drank with me.</i>

